    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model. We take actual free cash flows, project them out, and discount them back to present day.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Howmet generated <strong>$1.431 billion</strong> in free cash flow in FY2025.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>15% per year</strong> for 5 years based on extremely strong recent cash flow growth and high margins on aerospace parts.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>3.0% forever</strong> using the Gordon Growth Model.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>10%</strong> — our required rate of return.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (-$2.308B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding (404M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions</h2>
  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">15%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Howmet has shown stellar FCF growth recently (46% in 2025, 43% in 2024). 15% assumes robust but moderating demand in commercial aerospace and defense.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">10%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: 4.18%. Adding a standard equity risk premium puts our hurdle rate at 10%.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">3.0%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        In-line with long-term GDP growth, acknowledging that aerospace is a mature but critical industry.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
